│                                                                                                                              │
│ The assertion message strongly suggests that the vectorization logic is attempting to include a terminator instruction in    │
│ the set of instructions to be vectorized, which is illegal.                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ### 2. Analysis of the Reproducer IR                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ```llvm                                                                                                                      │
│ define void @test() gc "statepoint-example" personality ptr null {                                                           │
│ bb:                                                                                                                          │
│   %add = add i32 0, 0                                                                                                        │
│   %add1 = add i32 0, 0                                                                                                       │
│   %invoke = invoke i32 null(...) to label %bb2 unwind label %bb8                                                             │
│ bb2:                                                                                                                         │
│   %add3 = add i32 %invoke, 0                                                                                                 │
│   br label %bb4                                                                                                              │
│ bb4:                                                                                                                         │
│   %phi = phi i32 [ %add3, %bb2 ]                                                                                             │
│   %phi5 = phi i32 [ 0, %bb2 ]                                                                                                │
│   %phi6 = phi i32 [ %add, %bb2 ]                                                                                             │
│   %phi7 = phi i32 [ %add1, %bb2 ]                                                                                            │
│   ret void                                                                                                                   │
│ ...                                                                                                                          │
│ }                                                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ - The SLP vectorizer likely identifies the PHI nodes in block `bb4` as a potential vectorization candidate.                  │
│ - The operands of these PHIs come from different basic blocks.                                                               │
│ - `%phi6` and `%phi7` depend on `%add` and `%add1` from block `bb`.                                                          │
│ - `%phi` depends on `%add3` from block `bb2`, which in turn depends on the `%invoke` instruction in `bb`.                    │
│ - The `invoke` instruction is a terminator.                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The problem likely arises when the vectorizer tries to build a schedule for the operands. It traces back from the PHIs in    │
│ `bb4` to the instructions that produce their values. When it encounters `%invoke`, which is a terminator, it seems to handle │
│ it incorrectly.                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ### 3. Code Inspection                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ Let's examine `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp` around the assertion.                                        │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The function `extendSchedulingRegion` is responsible for checking if an instruction `V` can be included in the current       │
│ scheduling region, which is defined by `ScheduleStart` and `ScheduleEnd`.                                                    │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The assertion is:                                                                                                            │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                       │
│ assert(ScheduleEnd && "tried to vectorize a terminator?");                                                                   │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
│ This implies `ScheduleEnd` is `nullptr`. Looking at the call site in `tryScheduleBundle`:                                    │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                       │
│ // llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                                                           │
│ bool BoUpSLP::BlockScheduling::tryScheduleBundle(...) {                                                                      │
│   ...                                                                                                                        │
│   // Initialize the scheduling region.                                                                                       │
│   ScheduleStart = ScheduleEnd = Root;                                                                                        │
│   ...                                                                                                                        │
│   // Extend the scheduling region to cover all operands.                                                                     │
│   for (Value *V : Operands) {                                                                                                │
│     if (!extendSchedulingRegion(V, Instrs))                                                                                  │
│       return false;                                                                                                          │
│   }                                                                                                                          │
│   ...                                                                                                                        │
│ }                                                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
│ `ScheduleEnd` is initialized to `Root`. `Root` is the instruction that is the root of the current vectorization treelet. In  │
│ the case of PHI nodes, `Root` can be `nullptr`. If `Root` is `nullptr`, `ScheduleEnd` will also be `nullptr`, leading to the │
│ assertion failure when `extendScheduling_region` is called.                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The logic in `tryScheduleBundle` needs to handle the case where `Root` is `nullptr`. This typically happens when vectorizing │
│ a group of PHI nodes, as they don't have a common "root" instruction in the traditional sense within a single block.         │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ A simple fix is to skip the region extension logic if `ScheduleEnd` is `nullptr`. This is safe because if `ScheduleEnd` is   │
│ `nullptr`, it means we are processing PHI nodes, and their operands (which are in predecessor blocks) do not need to be      │
│ scheduled in the same region as the PHIs themselves. The operands will be handled when their respective blocks are           │
│ processed.                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ### 4. Proposed Fix                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ I will add a check at the beginning of `extendSchedulingRegion` to return `true` immediately if `ScheduleEnd` is `nullptr`.  │
│ This indicates that we are in a PHI-node vectorization scenario where the concept of a single-block scheduling region does   │
│ not apply to the operands.                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                       │
│ // In BoUpSLP::BlockScheduling::extendSchedulingRegion                                                                       │
│ bool BoUpSLP::BlockScheduling::extendSchedulingRegion(                                                                       │
│     Value *V, const InstructionsState &Instrs) {                                                                             │
│   // If the schedule region is not yet initialized, we can't extend it. This                                                 │
│   // happens when we have a group of PHIs.                                                                                   │
│   if (!ScheduleEnd)                                                                                                          │
│     return true;                                                                                                             │
│ ...                                                                                                                          │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ This change prevents the assertion by acknowledging that for PHI nodes, the operands are not part of the same scheduling     │
│ region and should not be processed by `extendSchedulingRegion`.                                                              │
