│ `invoke`) have failed because they leave the system in an inconsistent state, causing a different crash.                     │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The most direct and robust solution is to prevent the vectorizer from ever considering a terminator instruction as a         │
│ candidate for vectorization in the first place. The function `isVectorizable` in `SLPVectorizer.cpp` is the gatekeeper for   │
│ this. It checks if an instruction is a valid candidate to be part of a vectorization tree.                                   │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ By adding a check `!I->isTerminator()` to this function, I can ensure that no terminator instruction, including `invoke`,    │
│ will ever be processed by the downstream scheduling logic. This preemptively cuts off the problematic code path and is a     │
│ more fundamental fix than trying to patch the consequences in the scheduling or tree-building algorithms.                    │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ I will now use `sed` to add this check to the `isVectorizable` function.                                                     │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                      │
│ sed -i '/return I && !isa<PHINode>(I) && !I->isEHPad() &&/ s/$/ !I->isTerminator() &&/'                                      │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                                                              │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
